    "chemicalDescription": [
      "rh-Oligopeptide-4 is a single chain recombinant human peptide, produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is directly isolated from a human cell which codes for Thymosin Beta 4. It contains a maximum of 44 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or sugar. The protein consists of the proper sequence of the standard amino acids. Human Oligopeptide-16; TB4X; Thymosin Beta4; TMSB4"
